# Test hints for MultiService
# Multi-service example with HTTP, Socket, and File Monitor
type: multiservice
# mode: interpreter — compiled mode diverges from interpreter:
# socket welcome lines arrive before the harness's client subscribes
# (race only at compiled speed), and file events emit FILE MODIFIED
# instead of FILE CREATED / FILE DELETED. Both are real runtime
# parity gaps; revisit once the file-monitor + socket bring-up are
# fixed rather than papering over with per-platform expected files.
mode: interpreter
timeout: 20
skip-on-windows: Multi-service tests not supported on Windows CI
